      "content": "\"Observe them, men; their customs are a tangle of chaotic impulses, lacking the rational discipline we so naturally possess. They move with a primal fervor, a beautiful yet ultimately undisciplined spirit ill-suited for the fragile scaffolding of modern governance. Their internal arrangements are mere fleeting skirmishes, incapable of sustaining the grand architecture of law and industry. Therefore, it falls upon us, the enlightened, to impose the immutable logic of civilized society upon their volatile existence.\"",
      "source": "target",
